The paper deals with image processing techniques for enhancing visibility in hazy or foggy scenes, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The paper discusses various methods and provides a benchmark for evaluating these methods, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for image processing, which suggests that it could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or machine learning (cs.LG).
